  "prompt": "How do you block someone on Quora?",
  "response": "To block someone on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the person's profile:** Navigate to the profile of the user you want to block.\n\n2. **Find the block option:** Click on the three dots ( \u22ee ) typically found on their profile page, which may be located near their name or under their profile picture.\n\n3. **Select \"Block\":** From the dropdown menu, choose the \"Block\" option.\n\n4. **Confirm blocking:** You may be prompted to confirm that you want to block the user. Confirm your choice.\n\nOnce you block someone, they will not be able to follow you, see your activity, or interact with you on Quora. Additionally, you won't receive any notifications from them. If you ever want to unblock them, you can do so by going to your settings and managing your blocked users.",
